24:29.448 --> 24:35.236
that's psychologically a fact many times when we 
want to criticize something, we just want to

24:29.448 --> 24:35.236
launch out. One

24:38.000 --> 24:45.490
of the things that I have thought since I've been in 
A&M that makes it a, An interesting institution

24:45.892 --> 24:55.503
and different from others is the number of 
traditions that exist there carried on by the

24:45.892 --> 24:55.503
students from year to year. And I'm thinking in 
terms of old Yale practice, the silver taps, the

24:55.523 --> 25:04.553
bonfire, and things of that nature. How many of 
these were in existence during your years there?

25:08.978 --> 25:13.924
Well, those three or four ones that you mentioned 
were certainly We had silver taps, and it happened

25:14.866 --> 25:18.511
at least twice while I was there. And we had yell 
practice, which we thoroughly enjoyed, and I

25:20.775 --> 25:28.826
think that was something that brought us together 
and made us feel as one. And the general, of course,

25:30.649 --> 25:38.360
it was all cadet corps, except the casuals, who 
were World War I veterans. My freshman in South

25:40.323 --> 25:41.785
Wales, Not necessarily the World War. Well, some 
of them were veterans who had been, stayed out of

25:44.361 --> 25:48.366
school a while. And I know one of my real fine 
friends was a World War, had been in the Navy in

25:48.426 --> 25:53.191
